><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Toede</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>4</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>11/4/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>9:57:30 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">New Rules?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hello,<br>
<br>
It was brought to my attention today that some more rules were made by someone....  I just want to see if the info I got was near right and if so give some insight on each.<br>
<br>
One rule was your posting entity needs to have 40 planable people.  If that's the case I feel that number is too high by ten.  I think we can all agree that 30 is a good round number that can easily clear a plane in the alotted amount of time.  I understand the problem is having anyone and everyone posting raids and not being able to come near clearing a plane, but 40?  You can easily clear a plane with 18, I think 30 is more fair.<br>
<br>
The other rule I heard about was limiting invites to 6.  WHY?  What is the purpose of this rule?  Is it not the same purpose of the 2/3 rule?  Refer back to Derreks post, my guild and posting entity has no sks, no necromancers, no rogues, no bards, and few of some other classes....so what you're saying I should do is just go ahead and let that loot rot?  I can understand and work with 2/3 for the same reasons I've heard for this 6 invite thing, but 6 only?  It seems like it limits the amount of loot getting out to people that could actually use thereby reducing the number of times they need to visit the given plane more.  In short, limiting the invites to 6 adds to the problem more then it fixes it.<br>
<br>
That's all that I heard about.  I don't know who is making the rules or if even the rules have been made, but I do ask that you at least consider what I have said.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
